title: Materials and Biophysical Chemistry Laboratory
yc_attrs: This course can be applied towards the Sciences Yale College distributional requirement.
description:
A laboratory course covering physical methods and chemical synthesis in materials and biophysical chemistry. Techniques include solution phase synthesis, solid state synthesis, UV-Vis, fluorescence, optical microscopy, SEM, STM, single molecule fluorescence, and optical trapping methods.

After two terms of general chemistry with laboratory, or concurrently with CHEM 333.
regnotes:
1. There are four (4) laboratory sections; however, enrollment is limited due to instrumentation. Therefore, it is imperative that you contact the instructors with your preference ranking of three different sections to ensure everyone can be accommodated. Laboratory sections will begin on January 25th (see below).
2. Since Chem 335L is a full credit laboratory course, it meets twice a week - once for a laboratory session (Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday, or Thursday; 1:00-5:00pm, SCL-27) and once for a lecture (Friday; 1:30-2:20pm, SCL-18). Attendance at the Friday afternoon lectures is mandatory.
3. During the first (partial) week of classes, only the lecture component of Chem 335L will meet at 1:30pm on Wednesday (01/20) and Friday (01/22) to review material for the first experiment. Students should plan to attend both lectures, as each will cover different topics.
4. Laboratory sessions for Chem 335L will commence during the second (or first-full) week of classes at 1:00pm on Monday (01/25), Tuesday (01/26), Wednesday (01/27), and Thursday (01/28).
